<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Outrageous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Outrageous,</orth> 1) violent, atrocious: <bibl n="shak. luc 607" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 607</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.8.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 8, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.97" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 1, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 2, 139</bibl> (Ff <emph>villanous</emph>).<lb />2) excessive, exorbitant: <cit><quote>when thy poor heart beats with o. beating,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 3.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 2, 13</bibl></cit>.
